==English==

 
===Etymology===
From the word Nacre, an organic mixture of calcium carbonate (also known as Mother of Pearl).

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|Media:en-us-{{PAGENAME}}.ogg|Audio (US)}} \Na"cre*ous\

===Adjective===
1. Consisting of, or resembling, nacre.

2. Exhibiting lustrous or rainbow-like colors


===See also===
opalescent, opaline, pearlescent